titleStmt.title: Glosses on Priscian, Ars grammatica, in St Gall, Stiftsbibliothek, 904

editionStmt.p: Glosses from Priscian books 1–5 were published in R. Hofman, The Sankt Gall Priscian Commentary. Part 1 (2 vols, Münster, 1996).
All glosses published in digital edition by Pádraic Moran: http://www.stgallpriscian.ie

handDesc.summary: For details, see Hofman 1996, 12–25. Sequence of hands is A and B; then D, H, C. (Sequence of others not recoverable.) In some references, uncertainies are indicated with "?" or "/" (e.g. "#hand-G/C?"). These are left as is.
handDesc.handNote: Glossator B, Irish minuscule; helper of glossator A (e.g. col. 65b34r to end of col. 67)
Glossator C, Irish minuscule; after D and H, therefore writing on the Continent
Glossator D, Irish minuscule with Continental influence
Glossator F, Irish minuscule with Continental influence, similar to D
Glossator G, Caroline script; also wrote Old Irish glosses; after D, H, C
Glossator Z, Caroline script (5a m.s. a only)
Secondary hands not yet assigned; for details see notes in Hofman.
